Flatline detector
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We considered flatline as an extended time of inactivity in one or multiple
 leads.
 For detecting this, we developed 3 algorithms that analyse the variance,
 the derivative and the signal amplitude in order to implement the best
 performing approach: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
FL1=min\left\{ var(\mathrm{\mathbf{S_{i}}})\right\} \:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:FL2=min\left\{ mean\left(\frac{d\mathrm{\mathbf{S_{i}}}}{dt}\right)\right\} \:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:\:{\displaystyle FL3=min\left\{ \left|\boldsymbol{S_{i}}-mean(\boldsymbol{S_{i}})\right|\right\} }
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
