\begin_layout Section
Discussion
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During this work, we presented a mixed algorithm which includes a binary
 tree and a SQI based detector for the quality classification of ECG records.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The joint and individual performance was evaluated for all the detectors
 giving promising results.
 The best accuracy and sensitivity was obtained by the full detector based
 in SQI with almost a 94% of accuracy and 99% of sensitivity, followed by
 the RD with a accuracy of 93% and sensitivity of 98%.
 The best specificity was obtained by BT-RD with 88% followed by BT-FD with
 87%.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The performance of the binary tree is good but, comparing FL-HI and FL-SK-HI
 performance, we found that the SK detector does not make considerable contribut
ion.
 These could be explained because of the scarcity of spikes found in the
 databases used in these work.
 These aspect should be further studied in other databases, and maybe remove
 it for computational improvement.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Both SQI models detector's performance have the best accuracy and sensitivity.
 The results of the joint performance BT-RD and BT-FD were lower than we
 expected, we expected to achieve a better performance than the individual
 performance of RD and FD.
 These could be explained because the criterion used to label the ecgqdb,
 there are many acceptable records (according to our criterion) which contain
 flatline or huge impulses, were labelled as acceptable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For being a first approach, we are confidence with the results obtained.
 In following works, we are going to develop a better features model for
 the detector and reduce it to improve the computational cost.
 As we have seen several arguable labelling in the ecgqdb, we are considering
 to re-label it in order to improve the detector.
 For final improvement, we are going to test the algorithm in different
 databases for analysing the generalisation capability of the results obtained.
 
\end_layout

